# <type>(<scope>): <subject>   imperative, lowercase, no period
# ---- keep subject ≤50 chars, hard limit here: --------------------#
#
# Blank line above the body. Explain *what* and *why*, not *how*.
# Wrap body at 72 chars, which is here: ---------------------------------#
#
# Footer(s): BREAKING CHANGE: <desc>, Refs #<issue>, and
# Co-authored-by: Name <user@users.noreply.github.com>
# (one blank line before the footer block)
#
# ── Conventional Commits ── https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
#
# type:
#   feat      a new feature
#   fix       a bug fix
#   docs      documentation only
#   style     formatting; no behaviour change
#   refactor  neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf      performance improvement
#   test      adding or correcting tests
#   build     build system, dependencies (Brewfile, submodules)
#   ci        CI configuration
#   chore     maintenance, tooling
#
# scope (optional):  zsh  zellij  git  nvim  macos  theme
# breaking change:   append ! after type/scope  ->  feat(zsh)!: ...
#
# e.g.  fix(zsh): bind arrow keys via terminfo
#       feat(macos): add ghostty configuration
